API stands for Application programming interface


What is API ?
An application programming interface (API) is a way for two or more computer programs to communicate with each other

API has four parts
1)Endpoint: Sort of entry point/starting point
2)Path: location/path
3)Parmaters: parameters means kind of customization we required to do / 
4)Authenticatin : how much data acess we have

Example : http://api.openweathermap.org/data/3.0/onecall?lat={lat}&lon={lon}&lang={lang}
Here,
Enpoint is :http://api.openweathermap.org
Path is : http://api.openweathermap.org/data/3.0/
Parameter is : lat={lat}&lon={lon}&lang={lang}

JSON: Javascript Object Notion is one of the format we get while calling api


